headline: Floods Kill 30 in Jakarta as Over a Foot of Rain Falls
abstract: At least 43 people have been killed in the most intense rains to strike Jakarta, the country’s capital, since record keeping began.
lead_paragraph: JAKARTA, Indonesia — Flash floods killed at least 43 people and left hundreds of thousands homeless in Jakarta, the Indonesian capital, the authorities said on Friday, after the city’s most intense period of rainfall since record keeping began more than 20 years ago.
